      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions must replicate all five VAD operating points including hematocrit, temperature, and anticoagulant protocol; measurement uncertainty must be fully characterised.",
      "rationale": "Experimental data covers three of five required operating points; hematocrit variability and anticoagulant protocol are not fully matched to clinical VAD conditions. Achieved level 3 falls short of required level 5."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Normalised index of agreement and validation metric must be computed with experimental uncertainty bands; systematic bias must be below 15% across all operating points.",
      "rationale": "Validation metric computed for three operating points shows mean bias of 22%, exceeding the 15% threshold. Incomplete operating-point coverage prevents full output comparison at required level 5."
