      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The primary QoI (normalised index of hemolysis, NIH) must be directly traceable to the clinical endpoint; surrogate QoIs must be justified with sensitivity analysis.",
      "rationale": "NIH is used as the primary QoI and is clinically relevant, but sensitivity analysis linking NIH to clinical hemolysis threshold has not been formally documented. Achieved level 3 is one grade below required."
    },
    {
